choices.text: Given a string t, we will call it unbalanced if and only if the length of t is at least 2, and more than half of the letters in t are the same. For example, both voodoo and melee are unbalanced, while neither noon nor a is. You are given a string s consisting of lowercase letters. Determine if there exists a (contiguous) substring of s that is unbalanced. If the answer is positive, show a position where such a substring occurs in s.
